Analysis of Nmap Service Enumeration Scan
Executive Summary

An Nmap version detection scan (-sV) was conducted against the target host 172.16.59.129 from a Kali Linux system using the Metasploit db_nmap command.

The objective of the scan was to identify:

Active services
Open TCP ports
Service versions
Potential attack surface

The target appears to be Metasploitable 2, an intentionally vulnerable Linux virtual machine designed for penetration testing practice.

