Command Analysis
db_nmap -Pn -n -sV 172.16.59.129
Meaning of the Parameters
Option	Description
db_nmap	Executes Nmap through the Metasploit Framework and stores scan results in the Metasploit database.
-Pn	Skips host discovery and assumes the target is online. Useful when ICMP responses are filtered.
-n	Disables DNS resolution to speed up scanning.
-sV	Attempts to determine the version of services listening on open ports.
