Service Enumeration Analysis
FTP (21)
vsftpd 2.3.4
Observation

This is one of the most well-known vulnerable FTP servers.

Historically, compromised versions of vsftpd 2.3.4 have been associated with a backdoor that allows unauthorized shell access under specific circumstances. The version alone does not prove the backdoor is present, but it warrants investigation in a controlled lab.

Risk Level: High

